# TSDoc Conventions

When adding or refactoring JSDoc/TSDoc in TypeScript files, follow the [TSDoc guide](_reference/tsdoc-guide.md). Use **only tags defined in the TSDoc spec**; there is no `@property` tag in the standard.

## Summary

- **Block style:** One `/** ... */` block above each exported declaration. Avoid scattering inline comments on every member.
- **Standard tags only:** `@param`, `@returns`, `@remarks`, `@see`, `@example`, `@defaultValue`, `@typeParam`, `@throws`. Tag names are camelCase (e.g. `@defaultValue`). Do **not** use `@property`.
- **Interfaces/types:** Describe members and defaults in the **summary** and/or **@remarks** as prose.
- **Links:** In `@see` or in text, use `{@link SymbolOrUrl}` or `{@link url|label}`; TSDoc does not auto-link plain text after `@see`.
- **Reference:** Full rules in [_reference/tsdoc-guide.md](_reference/tsdoc-guide.md). Official tags: [StandardTags.ts](https://github.com/microsoft/tsdoc/blob/main/tsdoc/src/details/StandardTags.ts).

